==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰer-}}
From {{bor|en|la|inferō}}, from {{der|en|la|in-|id=in|gloss=in, at, on; into}} + {{der|en|la|ferō|gloss=bear, carry; suffer}} (cognate to {{cog|ang|beran}}, whence English {{m|en|bear}}), from {{der|en|itc-pro|*ferō}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰéreti||to bear, carry}}, from the root {{m|ine-pro|*bʰer-}}. Literally “carry forward”, equivalent to “bear in”, as in concluding from a premise.

